         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the divine spirits. To Athictus, son of Hermes, the underslave of Threptus (and) chief accountant of Sallustia Lucana. He lived for three years and three months, three days.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Tall "I"s in the first (second "I" in "Diis") and last (in "diebus") lines. Tall "T"s in lnes 2, 3, and 6 throughout but not in lines 4 and 5.</p>
            <p>Line 2: part of "P" and all of "T" and "I" at the end of the line are carved outside the campus within the molded boder.</p>
            <p>Line 3: "N" at the end of the line is carved outside the campus within the molded boder.</p>
            <p>Line 4: part of "R" and all of "I" at the end of the line are carved outside the campus within the molded boder.</p>
         </div>
